            <h1>Cities, Small Towns and Suburbs</h1>
            <h2 class="lead">How are community differents?</h2>
            <p>All communities are not the same. You will learn about the three different kinds of communities in this lesson. They are called urban, rural and suburban.</p>
            <h2 class="lead">I. Urban Communities</h2>
            <h3>1. Cities or towns are urban communities</h3>
            <p>Cities have lots of buildings and people. People often walk from place to place in a city. Sometimes they take a bus or taxi. Many people ride trains from one part of a city to another. Some people drive cars or bikes. People live in appartements in cities. There might be 50 or more homes in an appartment building. Where do you live?</p>
            <h3>2. Living in Urban communities</h3>
            <p>Cities are exciting. There are many stores and restaurants in a city. There are park and playgrounds, too. Most of the headquarter of  the great companies are there. There also many job there.</p>
            <p>Sometimes, cities are noisy. Cars honk their horns because of the traffic dram. People sing. Babies cry. Dogs bark. There are crowds in a city. There are lots of people on the sidewalks. Stores and restaurants are busy places, too. What do you like about cities?</p>
