            <h2 class="lead">III. Suburban Communities</h2>
            <h3>1. Suburbs are suburban communities</h3>
            <p>Suburbs are smaller than cities. They are bigger than small towns. There are neighbourhoods full home in suburbs. There are school, fire stations, police stations and hospitals. There are stores and gas stations. There are parks and other places to play.</p>
            <h3>2. Living in Suburban communities</h3>
            <p>Many families live in suburbs. Some people live in a houses. Some people live in appartments. Lots of home have yards. Most people drive cars in a suburb. People drive to work. They drive to shopping malls. There are lots of parking in suburbs. What else might you see in a suburb?</p>
